<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
    xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
    xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
    metal:use-macro="standard_template/macros/page">
<metal:fill fill-slot="body">
<p>The Python Cheese Shop is a repository of software for the Python
programming language.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 2em">
<strong>Customer</strong>: Now then, some cheese please, my good man.
<br />
<strong>Owner</strong>: (lustily) Certainly, sir. What would you like?
<br />
<strong>Customer</strong>: Well, eh, how about a little red Leicester.
<br />
<strong>Owner</strong>: I'm, a-fraid we're fresh out of red Leicester, sir.
</p>
<p>
There are currently <strong tal:content="app/store/count_packages" />
packages in the Cheese Shop. You may:
</p>
<ul>
<li><a tal:attributes="href python:
app.link_action('search_form')">Search</a></li>
<li><a tal:attributes="href python:app.link_action('browse')">Browse the
tree of packages</a></li>
<li><a tal:attributes="href python:app.link_action('index')">View a flat
list of all packages</a></li>
<li><a tal:attributes="href python:app.link_action('submit_form')">Submit package information</a> 
(note that you must <a tal:attributes="href python:app.link_action('register_form')">
register to submit</a>)</li>
</ul>

<p>Last 20 updates:</p>
<table class="list">
<tr><th>Updated</th><th>Package</th><th>Description</th></tr>

<tal:for-release repeat="release python: app.store.latest_releases()">
<tal:let define="name python: release[0]; 
 version python: release[1]; 
 date python: release[2]; 
 summary python: release[3]">

<tr tal:attributes="class repeat/release/parity">
 <td tal:content="python:str(date)[:10]">date</td>
 <td tal:content="structure python: app.packageLink(name, version)">link</td>
 <td tal:content="summary">summary</td>
</tr>

</tal:let>
</tal:for-release>

<tr><td id="last" colspan="3"></td></tr>
</table>

</metal:fill>
</html>
